name: CMIOExtensionStreamProperties
desc: An object that describes the properties of an extension stream.

items.name: init(dictionary: [CMIOExtensionProperty : CMIOExtensionPropertyState<AnyObject>])
items.desc: Creates a properties object that provides the specified properties and default states.

items.name: var sinkBuffersRequiredForStartup: Int?
items.desc: The number of buffers the stream requires for startup.

items.name: var sinkEndOfData: Int?
items.desc: A value that indicates whether the stream has reached its end.

items.name: var activeFormatIndex: Int?
items.desc: The index of the active format.

items.name: var maxFrameDuration: CMTime?
items.desc: The maximum duration of a frame.

items.name: var propertiesDictionary: [CMIOExtensionProperty : CMIOExtensionPropertyState<AnyObject>]
items.desc: A dictionary representation of the property state.

items.name: func setPropertyState(CMIOExtensionPropertyState<AnyObject>?, forProperty: CMIOExtensionProperty)
items.desc: Sets the state of the specified property.
